# Security & User Data Rules

## Core principle

User psychological data (dreams) is sensitive personal data.

## Data classification

Treat as sensitive:
- dream content
- emotional states
- personal narratives
- session history

## Rules

- Never log raw dream text in plaintext logs
- Mask sensitive data in logs if needed
- Do not expose user data in error messages

## Authentication

- Telegram ID is primary identity
- Mini App uses Telegram initData validation
- Backend must verify identity from trusted source

## Data access

- Users can only access their own data
- No cross-user data leakage allowed
- Group sessions must isolate participant views

## Storage

- Encrypt sensitive fields if possible (future enhancement)
- Avoid storing unnecessary raw metadata

## AI safety

- AI outputs are non-deterministic interpretations
- Must not be presented as medical/clinical truth

## Logging rules

- No raw personal content in logs
- Use IDs instead of content where possible

## Forbidden

- sharing user data between sessions
- exposing raw dreams in admin tools without auth